    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;transmutation&nbsp;[earth];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;cleric/oracle 2, druid 2, hunter 2, magus 2, ranger 2;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;creature touched<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 minute/level<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Fortitude negates (harmless);&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>This spell allows the target to cause the ground to rise up beneath him. As a swift action, the target can cause the ground to rise 5 feet, while all adjacent squares are treated as steep slopes (<i>Core Rulebook</i> 428). The <i>groundswell</i> precludes flanking from creatures standing at lower elevations than the target. If the target moves after creating a <i>groundswell</i>, the ground returns to its normal elevation at the end of his turn; otherwise, it remains in place until the target moves or uses a swift action to return the ground to normal. A <i>groundswell</i> cannot increase elevation of the ground beyond 5 feet.</p>\n</div>\n",
